	'_aqb_commission_mass_payment_API_info' => '<p><i>If you want to use paypal Mass Payment feature you need to get your credentials in your account on paypal. How to do this:</i></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Log in to your PayPal Premier or Business account</li> 
				<li>Click the <b>Profile</b> subtab located in the top navigation area</li>
				<li>Click the <b>API Access</b> link under the Account Information header</li> 
				<li>Click the <b>Request API Credentials</b> link in the right side</li>
				<li>Choose <b>Request API signature</b> option and click on <b>Agree and Submit</b> button</li>
				<li>Now you can see your API <b>username</b>, <b>password</b> and <b>signature</b>. You need to put them to Forced Matrix settings her <a href="{0}modules/index.php?r=aqb_affiliate/administration/settings"/>{0}modules/index.php?r=aqb_affiliate/administration/settings</a></li>
			</ul>',
	'_aqb_commission_mass_payment_IPN_info' => '<p>If you don\'t want to process all sent payments manually after payment, you need to set IPN in your paypal account and in Dolphin\'s Payment module.</p>
		  <p>How to do this:</p>
			<ul>
						<li>Log in to your PayPal Premier or Business account</li> 
						<li>Click the <b>Profile</b> subtab located in the top navigation area</li>
						<li>Click the <b> Instant Payment Notification Preferences</b> link under the <b>Selling Preferences</b> header</li> 
						<li> Choose the <b>Receive IPN messages (Enabled)</b> option and put to <b>Notification URL</b> text box <b>Data return URL</b> link from <a href="{0}m/payment/admin/">{0}m/payment/admin/</a> page from PayPal area and click Save</li>
						<li> Go to <a href="{0}m/payment/admin/"> {0}m/payment/admin/</a> page  and in <b>Process type</b> choose IPN type and then click Save</li>
			</ul>',
